  "title": "ENVIRONMENTAL CONTROL OFFICER (ECO)",
  "description": "<h1>Job Description</h1>\n<ul>\n  <li>Ensure compliance with the latest environmental regulations.</li>\n  <li>Prepare and implement Site Environmental Control Measures.</li>\n  <li>Identify environmental issues and recommend measures to rectify the irregularities.</li>\n  <li>Liaise with the government authorities, client and external provider on all environmental control issues.</li>\n  <li>Perform ECO duties as assigned</li>\n  <li>Experienced in HDB, LTA and PUB projects is an added advantage.</li>\n</ul>\n<h1><strong>Requirements</strong></h1>\n<ul>\n  <li>Possess at least a Specialist Diploma in WSH and/or Bachelor’s Degree in Workplace safety and health (WSH)-related and certificate in ECO;</li>\n  <li>MOM registered Environmental Control Officer and NEA registered ECO.</li>\n  <li>At least 5 year(s) of working experience in Civil works is preferred</li>\n</ul>",
